{
  "text": "At present, however, the model can at least be regarded as offering a heuristic that provides a way of understanding and empirically investigating the choices involved in radicalization and deradicalization which, in the words of [CITATION_1] , assumes that radicalized individuals and \"terrorists are ordinary people (to the extent that they are not distinguishable from other \"ordinary\" people) who make choices in the contexts in which they find themselves\" and \"that choices made by individuals are meaningful for the person making those choices\" (p. 588).",
  "citation_candidates": [
